Package: CurVol
Type: Package
Title: Curve Data Volatility Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Kelly Ramsay, Gregory Rice, Tony Wirjanto, Yuqian Zhao
Maintainer: Yuqian Zhao <y.zhao@essex.ac.uk>
Description: The CurVol package provides useful functions to analyse the volatility of functional time series data. Methods and tools in this package cover the hypothesis testing, model estimation, and backtesting Value-at-Risk in a series of papers including: 1). Aue, A., Horvath, L., F. Pellatt, D. (2017). Functional generalized autoregressive conditional heteroskedasticity. Journal of Time Series Analysis, 38(1), 3-21. 2). Cerovecki, C., Francq, C., Hormann, S., Zakoian, J. M. (2019). Functional GARCH models: The quasi-likelihood approach and its applications. Journal of Econometrics, 209(2), 353-375. 3). Hormann, S., Horvath, L., Reeder, R. (2013). A functional version of the ARCH model. Econometric Theory, 29(2), 267-288. 4). Rice, Wirjanto, and Zhao (2020) Tests for conditional heteroscedasticity of functional data, Journal of Time Series Analysis. 5).Rice, Wirjanto, and Zhao (2020) Forecasting Value at Risk via intra-day return curves, International Journal of Forecasting. 6).Rice, Wirjanto, and Zhao (2020) Functional GARCH-X models with an application to forecasting crude oil return curves, Working paper.
